evening discussion with representative zoe lofgren stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff calendar evening discussion with representative zoe lofgren go back details october 19 2011 from 4 00 pm 5 00 pm room 190 representative zoe lofgren a stanford university alumna represents california's 16th congressional district and chairs the california democratic congressional delegation as a member of the house judiciary committee and the science space and technology committee she has led the way on issues relating to technology and civil liberties recently she has been been a vocal opponent of the protect ip act and hr 1981 protecting children from internet pornographers act of 2011 if passed these acts would dramatically alter the government's power over the functioning of the internet and expand its access to information about people's online activities representative lofgren will share her views on these crucial and timely issues with the stanford law community hosted by slata contact alexandra moss ahmoss stanford edu cloudy 45 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
